### `instagram['key']` — Index Access

Access individual fields using dictionary-style bracket notation.

```python
print(instagram['Username'])
print(instagram['Profile Name'])
print(instagram['Followers'])
print(instagram['Following'])
print(instagram['Number of Posts'])
print(instagram['Bio'])
print(instagram['Profile Picture URL'])
print(instagram['Is Business Account?'])
print(instagram['Connected to FB?'])
print(instagram['External URL'])
print(instagram['Joined Recently?'])
print(instagram['Business Category Name'])
print(instagram['Is Private?'])
print(instagram['Is Verified?'])
```

**All valid keys:**

| Key | Type | Description |
|-----|------|-------------|
| `'Username'` | str | Account handle |
| `'Profile Name'` | str | Display name |
| `'URL'` | str | Full profile URL |
| `'Followers'` | str | Follower count |
| `'Following'` | str | Following count |
| `'Number of Posts'` | str | Total posts |
| `'Bio'` | str | Profile biography |
| `'Profile Picture URL'` | str | Direct URL to avatar image |
| `'Is Business Account?'` | bool | Business account flag |
| `'Connected to FB?'` | bool | Facebook link flag |
| `'External URL'` | str | Bio link (if any) |
| `'Joined Recently?'` | bool | New account flag |
| `'Business Category Name'` | str | Business category label |
| `'Is Private?'` | bool | Private account flag |
| `'Is Verified?'` | bool | Verified badge flag |

---

### `instagram.print_profile_data()`

Prints a formatted summary of all collected fields to the terminal.

```python
instagram.print_profile_data()
```

Useful for quick inspection without manually iterating the dictionary.

---

### `instagram.save_data()`

Saves the profile data to a `.txt` file on disk. The tool creates a local directory named after the username and writes the data as serialized JSON inside it.

```python
instagram.save_data()
# Creates: ./nasa/nasa.txt  (or similar path)
```

---

### `instagram.scrape_posts()`

Downloads publicly available photos from the profile into the local username directory.

```python
instagram.scrape_posts()
# Downloads images to: ./nasa/
```

> Only works on public accounts. Private accounts will yield no photos.

---

### `repr(instagram)` — Debug Representation

```python
print(repr(instagram))
