## Complete Working Example

```python
from InstagramOSINT import *

# Instantiate — scraping runs automatically
instagram = InstagramOSINT(https://www.instagram.com/jorayev_atajan77?igsh=bTU5dmlraDA3M2J6nasa')

# --- Access individual fields ---
print("Username:      ", instagram['Username'])
print("Display Name:  ", instagram['Profile Name'])
print("Followers:     ", instagram['Followers'])
print("Following:     ", instagram['Following'])
print("Posts:         ", instagram['Number of Posts'])
print("Bio:           ", instagram['Bio'])
print("External URL:  ", instagram['External URL'])
print("Verified:      ", instagram['Is Verified?'])
print("Private:       ", instagram['Is Private?'])
print("Business:      ", instagram['Is Business Account?'])
print("On Facebook:   ", instagram['Connected to FB?'])
print("New Account:   ", instagram['Joined Recently?'])
print("Profile Pic:   ", instagram['Profile Picture URL'])

# --- Print everything at once ---
instagram.print_profile_data()

# --- Save to disk ---
instagram.save_data()

# --- Download public photos ---
instagram.scrape_posts()
```

